  "prompt": "Which is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Coffee County AL?",
  "response": "Finding the right inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center is crucial for effective recovery. While I can\u2019t provide specific recommendations, here are a few reputable rehab centers near Coffee County, Alabama, that you might consider:\n\n### 1. **Bradford Health Services - Warrior, AL**\n   - **Location:** Warrior, AL (approx. 2.5 hours from Coffee County)\n   - **Services:** Offers inpatient and outpatient treatment programs, detox services, and aftercare planning.\n   - **Specialties:** Alcohol and drug addiction treatment.\n   - **Website:** [Bradford Health Services](https://www.bradfordhealth.com/)\n\n### 2. **Bridge Way Recovery Center - Dothan, AL**\n   - **Location:** Dothan, AL (approx. 1 hour from Coffee County)\n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient treatment, detox, and dual diagnosis care.\n   - **Specialties:** Treats substance abuse and co-occurring mental health disorders.\n   - **Website:** [Bridge Way Recovery Center](https://www.bridgewayrecovery.com/)\n\n### 3. **Foundations Recovery Center - Huntsville, AL**\n   - **Location:** Huntsville, AL (approx. 3 hours from Coffee County)\n   - **Services:** Inpatient treatment, detox, and holistic therapies.\n   - **Specialties:** Focuses on treating addiction and underlying mental health conditions.\n   - **Website:** [Foundations Recovery Center](https://www.foundationsrecoverynetwork.com/)\n\n### 4. **The Recovery Center USA - Montgomery, AL**\n   - **Location:** Montgomery, AL (approx. 2 hours from Coffee County)\n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient programs, detox, and relapse prevention.\n   - **Specialties:** Alcohol and drug addiction treatment.\n   - **Website:** [The Recovery Center USA](https://www.therecoverycenterusa.com/)\n\n### 5. **BayView Center for Mental Health - Mobile, AL**\n   - **Location:** Mobile, AL (approx. 3.5 hours from Coffee County)\n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient treatment, detox, and dual diagnosis care.\n   - **Specialties:** Substance abuse and mental health treatment.\n   - **Website:** [BayView Center](https://www.bayviewcenter.com/)\n\n### Tips for Choosing a Rehab Center:\n- **Accreditation:** Ensure the facility is accredited by organizations like the Joint Commission or CARF.\n- **Treatment Approach:** Look for programs that offer evidence-based therapies (e.g., CBT, DBT, MAT).\n- **Specialized Care:** Consider if you need dual diagnosis treatment or specific therapies (e.g., trauma-informed care).\n- **Cost and Insurance:** Verify if the center accepts your insurance or offers payment plans.\n\nIt\u2019s a good idea to contact these centers directly to discuss your needs and verify their services. You can also consult with a healthcare provider or addiction specialist for personalized recommendations.",
